:JOURNEY
Reading Gardens of the Moon
Section
Enjoyment
- Opening battle | 2 | Deliberately confusing | Felt like the book did not want me
- Pages 100 to 250 | 3 | Slow coherence | Things begin to connect with many notes taken
- Pages 250 to 500 | 5 | Fully clicks | The moment Erikson's project becomes clear
- The ending | 4 | Conditional payoff | Demands commitment to nine more books to land

:NOTE
Read a brief plot summary after the first 100 pages. It is not cheating. It is \
what Erikson's audience has quietly always done, and no one who loves this \
series will judge you for it.

